(1, 'Un Hardware Embebido para Implementación de un Control de Seguimiento en RMRs', 1, 'pablo.acm.ti@gmail.com', 29, 6, 'HARDWARE Estiudiante', '<p>The implementation of a hierarchical controller for the trajectory tracking control of a wheeled mobile robot (WMR) is presented in this work. The experimental development of such a controller is performed with the low-cost embedded hardware Jetson TK1 from NVIDIA. In the programming of the controller, free license software with short learning curve is used. To validate the performance of the embedded hardware, a comparison between the results obtained from the WMR in closed-loop is presented when using: a) the embedded hardware Jetson TK1 and b) the fast prototyping DS1104 board from dSPACE. The experimental results show that the Jetson TK1 board could be suitable for the control of autonomous mechatronic systems.</p>\r\n', 'Pablo Campos M.', 'Juanito Perez L.', NULL, NULL, 'Un_Hardwarpablo.acm.ti@gmail.com2018-08-21_02_17_39.docx', '<p>Embedded hardware, Jetson TK1, DS1104, Trajectory tracking, Wheeled mobile robot, Hierarchical controller&nbsp;The implementation of a hierarchical controller for the trajectory tracking control of a wheeled mobile robot (WMR) is presented in this work. The experimental development of such a controller is performed with the low-cost embedded hardware Jetson TK1 from NVIDIA. In the programming of the controller, free license software with short learning curve is used. To validate the performance of the embedded hardware, a comparison between the results obtained from the WMR in closed-loop is presented when using: a) the embedded hardware Jetson TK1 and b)&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2018-09-06 03:03:46', '2018-08-21', 1, 0, 0, '<p>se necesitan algunas modificaciones impuestas por los revisores&nbsp;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, '<p>el revisor solicito modificaciones.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-28 00:00:00', '2018-08-21 02:38:39', '81', 'UCM', 'juan@perez.cl', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'uploads/Un_Hardwarpablo.acm.ti@gmail.com2018-08-21_02_17_39.docx', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '2018-08-21', 1, 2, 3, 3, '2018-09-06', 3, '2018-09-06', NULL),
(2, 'Detección de Cambios en Reservorios Acuiferos Naturales basados en el Indice de Sequía', 1, 'pablo.acm.ti@gmail.com', 30, 13, 'NDVI, NDWI, NDDI, Landsat 7-ETM, Landsat 8 OLI/TIRS, Change Detections   ', '<p>The purpose of this work is the benefit exploitation of spectral indices such as NDVI, NDWI and NDDI for obtaining drought maps. To this objective, the geographical region of Poopo Lake (Bolivia) is selected as a study area. A set of multitemporal multiband scenes of this geographical area, sensed by Landsat7-ETM+ and Landsat8-OLI/TIRS sensors have been chosen. Experiments on this images datasets provide encouraging results which may be further used for the analysis of change detection, the decision-making and implementing future action plans.</p>\r\n', 'Pablo Campos M.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Detecciónpablo.acm.ti@gmail.com2018-08-25_22_20_58.docx', '<p>The purpose of this work is the benefit exploitation of spectral indices such as NDVI, NDWI and NDDI for obtaining drought maps. To this objective, the geographical region of Poopo Lake (Bolivia) is selected as a study area. A set of multitemporal multiband scenes of this geographical area, sensed by Landsat7-ETM+ and Landsat8-OLI/TIRS sensors have been chosen. Experiments on this images datasets provide encouraging results which may be further used for the analysis of change detection, the decision-making and implementing future action plans.</p>\r\n', '2018-08-27 21:41:06', '2018-08-25', 2, 0, 0, '<p>cumple con el formato y la informaci&oacute;n es correcta.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, '', '2018-09-18 00:00:00', '2018-08-27 16:20:45', '81', 'UCM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'uploads/Detecciónpablo.acm.ti@gmail.com2018-08-25_22_20_58.docx', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '2018-08-27', 1, 1, 3, 3, '2018-08-27', 3, '2018-08-27', NULL),
(3, 'Sistema Supervisor para Detección y Diagnostico de Fallas en Plantas de Agua Potable Usando Motores Difusos', 1, 'pablo.acm.ti@gmail.com', 29, 3, 'NDVI, NDWI, NDDI, Landsat 7-ETM, Landsat 8 OLI/TIRS, Change Detections   ', '<p>The purpose of this work is the benefit exploitation of spectral indices such as NDVI, NDWI and NDDI for obtaining drought maps. To this objective, the geographical region of Poopo Lake (Bolivia) is selected as a study area. A set of multitemporal multiband scenes of this geographical area, sensed by Landsat7-ETM+ and Landsat8-OLI/TIRS sensors have been chosen. Experiments on this images datasets provide encouraging results which may be further used for the analysis of change detection, the decision-making and implementing future action plans.</p>\r\n', 'Marco Morales C.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sistema_Supablo.acm.ti@gmail.com2018-08-26_20_04_30.docx', '<p>The purpose of this work is the benefit exploitation of spectral indices such as NDVI, NDWI and NDDI for obtaining drought maps. To this objective, the geographical region of Poopo Lake (Bolivia) is selected as a study area. A set of multitemporal multiband scenes of this geographical area, sensed by Landsat7-ETM+ and Landsat8-OLI/TIRS sensors have been chosen. Experiments on this images datasets provide encouraging results which may be further used for the analysis of change detection, the decision-making and implementing future action plans.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-04 00:41:17', '2018-08-26', 3, 5, 7, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2018-09-03 21:41:17', '81', 'UCM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'uploads/Sistema_Supablo.acm.ti@gmail.com2018-08-26_20_04_30.docx', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '2018-09-03', 1, 3, 3, 3, NULL, 3, NULL, NULL),
(4, 'Topologia de Amplificador de Baixo Ruído CMOS utilizando Indutor Ativo Compact Wu Folded ', 1, 'mtoranzo@ucm.cl', 31, 2, 'NDVI, NDWI, NDDI, Landsat 7-ETM, Landsat 8 OLI/TIRS, Change Detections   ', '<p>This work presents a topology proposal of a 0.35um CMOS cascode low noise amplifier using an active inductor. The inductance required to output of cascode pair is synthesized by an active inductor in Compact Wu Folded configuration. The LNA presents a gain of 12.04 dB with a noise figure of 4.78 dB at 1.8 GHz. The layout is presented occupying an active area of 0.165 mm2. The results are satisfactory, validating a compact design and demonstrating the technical feasibility of this topology in the band of interest.</p>\r\n', 'Jose Rangel M.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Topologia_mtoranzo@ucm.cl2018-08-27_18_12_54.docx', '<p>This work presents a topology proposal of a 0.35um CMOS cascode low noise amplifier using an active inductor. The inductance required to output of cascode pair is synthesized by an active inductor in Compact Wu Folded configuration. The LNA presents a gain of 12.04 dB with a noise figure of 4.78 dB at 1.8 GHz. The layout is presented occupying an active area of 0.165 mm2. The results are satisfactory, validating a compact design and demonstrating the technical feasibility of this topology in the band of interest.This work presents a topology proposal of a 0.35um CMOS cascode low noise amplifier using an active inductor. The inductance required to output of cascode pair is synthesized by an active inductor in Compact Wu Folded configuration. The LNA presents a gain of 12.04 dB with a noise figure of 4.78 dB at 1.8 GHz. The layout is presented occupying an active area of 0.165 mm2. The results are satisfactory, validating a compact design and demonstrating the technical feasibility of this topology in the band of interest.</p>\r\n', '2018-08-27 21:17:27', '2018-08-27', 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '5', 'UCM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 